reviews.snippet:
As someone who’s had kebabs across the Middle East, Europe and beyond, I can confidently say Halal Sakura in Tokyo offers something refreshingly unique. The kebab here has its own signature flavour—succulent, well-spiced, and served with a side of surprise: chopsticks! First time eating kebab this way, and it actually made the whole experience even more memorable. The Central Asian twist adds depth to the usual kebab fare, and it works brilliantly.

Bonus points for the clean and accessible prayer space upstairs, which is such a thoughtful touch for Muslim travellers. If you’re in Tokyo and craving halal comfort food with a twist, this spot is a must.
